properties.name: Capernwray Hall
properties.description: Posted by RazmondThis little mid-size, economy estate (although very castle like) has had a profound effect on bazillions of peoples lives. Cross cultural, rural, peaceful... The spark that ignited this vision so long ago has enflamed relationships with Christ--drawing individuals closer, learning how to live out faith, and truly study the Word of God. My life will never be the same. Capernwray Hall is a 19th-century mansion set in 175 acres of parkland, just south of England\'s famous Lake District, and west of the rugged crags of the Yorkshire Dales National Park. Capernwray Hall was built in the mid-1800\'s as a private home for the Lord Lieutenant of the county of Lancaster. The Scottish border is 70 miles (110 km) to the north; to the east lie the Yorkshire Dales with their beautiful waterfalls and rugged crags. To the south is the ancient City of Lancaster. Manchester with its international airport is just over an hour away.

properties.name: Tauernhof Bible School
properties.description: Posted by RazmondÂ Coburgstrasse, AustriaHere\'s a bit of info on Tauernhof. It seemed the sun was always shinging, great food was always to be had, great people to surround you, majestic mountains to envelop you. It\'s easily one of my favorite places on the planet. Tauernhof is an international Bible school and retreat centre, offering short-term and practical Bible training and camps for young adults. It is located directly in the Austrian Alps in the picturesque resort town of Schladming, which is cradled between two majestic mountain ranges about 70 km southeast of Salzburg. Tauernhof itself is a centre with a warm, friendly atmosphere, accommodating up to 45 people. It is our desire to offer programmes through which people may get to know the Lord Jesus Christ more personally by sharing and enjoying His life. We want to promote the growth of the Christian as a whole person - spiritually, mentally, and physically. Tauernhof is also a great place to be refreshed while enjoying the breathtaking beauty of God\'s creation. It is for these purposes that our programs, which are described here, have been designed.
